            .panel-body
              %h4 What is MyApnea.org?
              %p MyApnea.org is a network created by people with sleep apnea to empower others like you and us get the answers WE want and need through sharing and promoting research. MyApnea.org is what’s called patient-powered research. You and others like us share health information, discuss experiences regarding treatment, and express views on future research projects directly with researchers and sleep experts that can make a difference. In return, you will get easy to use tools to track your health and learn from others about treatments, symptoms and coping with sleep apnea in order to take control of your life.
              %h4 What is sleep apnea?
              %p Sleep apnea is a common and potentially life threatening sleep and breathing disorder. With sleep apnea, breathing is repeatedly interrupted during sleep, sometimes hundreds of times during the night and often for a minute or longer. Left untreated, sleep apnea increases the risk for high blood pressure, heart attack, stroke and other medical conditions. It has been estimated that at least 18 million Americans have sleep apnea, but it often goes unrecognized and untreated. Once diagnosed, sleep apnea can be successfully treated and should not interfere with your job or quality of life.
              %h4 Who can join MyApnea.org?
              %p Membership is open to any person who has been told by a doctor that they have sleep apnea and wants to share and learn from others in order to shape future research and treatments. Parents and caregivers of family members with sleep apnea will also be able to join and help their loved ones participate and complete surveys
              %h4 What is MyApnea.org?
              %p
                You can contact the SAPCON study staff about any questions, concerns, or complaints you have at support@myapnea.org. If you want to speak with someone not directly involved in this research study, please contact the Partners Human Research Committee office. You can call them at 617-424-4100. You can talk to them about:
                %ul
                  %li Your rights as a research subject
                  %li Your concerns about the research
                  %li A complaint about the research
              %h4 Where can I find more information about sleep apnea?
              %p
                Other sites you might want to check for more information are:
                %ul
                  %li
                    %a{:href => "http://www.sleepapnea.org", :target => "_blank"} www.sleepapnea.org
                  %li
                    %a{:href => "http://healthysleep.med.harvard.edu", :target => "_blank"} healthysleep.med.harvard.edu
                  %li
                    %a{:href => "http://www.nhlbi.nih.gov/health/health-topics/topics/sleepapnea", :target => "_blank"} www.nhlbi.nih.gov/health/health-topics/topics/sleepapnea
              %h4 Where can I find more information about the Patient Centered OUtcomes Research Institute?
              %p
                Please visit
