                %h3 Participation
          #collapseThree.panel-collapse.collapse
            .panel-body
              %h4 How is MyApnea.Org organized?
              %p The Patient Centered Outcomes Research Institute (PCORI) funds MyApnea.org (link to PCORI). PCORI’s goals are to support comparative clinical effectiveness research that will provide the evidence needed to help patients and their caregivers make better-informed decisions on health care. To accomplish this, MyApnea.org asks you to participate in a study. You’ll be asked to take easy-to-complete surveys and join other study activities. As we post new surveys we’ll invite you to complete them too. You’ll also receive special invitations periodically (at least twice per year) to participate in other parts of the study. We will only ask for your participation in such a study after you've consented to that specific study. Some examples: download information from your PAP machine (from your card or modem), mobile apps to track your activity or heart measures (such as heart rate), and sensors to measure things (like ECGs, sleep, blood pressure, weight). You will see all your study activities and special invitations on your homepage once you join the study.
              %h4 How long will I be in the study?
              %p We would like to keep you part of our community for at least the next 2+ years, and preferably longer. Keeping in touch with you and checking on your health from time to time is very important to help us look at the long-term effects of sleep apnea and its effects on your health. We plan to do this by contacting you at least twice a year.
              %h4 Can I stop being in the study?
              %p Yes. You can stop at any time. We won’t delete the information about you that we’ve already collected, but we will stop collecting any new information and will stop contacting you. To stop participating in the network, please send an email to the study staff at: support@myapnea.org.
              %h4 What's expected of me?
              %p
                Ideally, we want you to:
                %ul
                  %li 1. answer the study's health-related questions
                  %li 2. check in regularly so we have your most up-to-date information
                  %li 3. let us know which other studies and special invitations you want to accept and participate in
                  %li 4. participate for at least 2 years so we can track how your health changes over time
              %h4 What are the surveys all about?
              %p If you agree to participate in the MyApnea.org network, you will be asked to complete a series of surveys about your sleep, symptoms and health. The surveys will ask about such things as when you were diagnosed with sleep apnea, treatments you have used, medical illnesses such as high blood pressure, and your energy level. The basic surveys will take less than 30 minutes to complete for most people. Some of them may ask for sensitive information such as next of kin or detailed contact information. The surveys will help us learn how to best treat and manage sleep apnea. They will also help us learn what is most important to you about your treatment and disease management. You can do each survey online or on your smartphone whenever you can.
              %h4 How often do I have to take these surveys?
              %p
                You will be asked to update information on these surveys every 2 to 6 months or as your health changes. In addition, you’ll receive occasional special invitations to participate in other studies or take special surveys, depending on your specific health status. Surveys will usually give you an estimate of the time required to complete it so you can do it when it is most convenient for you.
